transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I received a refill prescription through Score Blue and I'm trying to find out something.

Speaker 1: Has something changed with the prescription? What was your last name?

Speaker 2: Benjamin. Spell it for me, please.

Speaker 1: B-E-N-N-A-M-A-N. Raymond?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. And what, are you like seeing different markings on the pills or what's going on?

Speaker 2: I don't see anything that should have been different. What is the...

Speaker 1: Different markings. It used to be, I guess you can see what I'm getting, what am I getting there?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you should just be getting our generic Viagra the whole time.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so what's changed is I used to get it and it used to have just a 100 on it.

Speaker 2: Now it says AC 3440 and it doesn't seem to do anything.

Speaker 1: When did you see that switch happen?

Speaker 2: Well, I just renewed this within the past two months, but when I used to get it, it used to say 100 on it.

Speaker 1: Now it says AC...

Speaker 2: Oh, I get you. You know what? I really couldn't say, Mr. Benjamin, what I would imagine is happening

Speaker 1: if you're seeing different markings on the pills.

Speaker 2: What I mean by I can't say is I just wasn't here in 2022,

Speaker 1: so I'm not sure who the manufacturer of the medication was,

Speaker 2: but the manufacturer has probably switched since you started back in 2025.

Speaker 1: I'm sure we still carry that other version, but you probably just got something else.

Speaker 2: But, so the previous pills worked for you, these ones didn't.

Speaker 1: Yes, the previous ones worked. The 100s that I used to get worked, and like I said, these didn't do nothing.

Speaker 2: And did you want to try to see about getting that old pill again?

Speaker 1: Yeah, if I could get the old ones again, yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, I think we still do have those.

Speaker 1: Yeah, the problem is, it's like I've gotten two months of these and they're no good to me.

Speaker 2: Would I do send them back to you or do you guys credit me or do anything for me?

Speaker 1: What I can do if you want, I can send you a replacement order out for you.

Speaker 2: I'll send you 10 of these other pills to see if you do like them,

Speaker 1: and then if you do, we can go from there. We can switch the prescription over for you.

Speaker 2: Okay, all right, so when can you do that?

Speaker 1: I'll do that for you today, Mr. Benneman, that's no issue.

Speaker 2: Okay, like I said, the ones that said 100 on them worked. These ones here do nothing.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, no problem.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I'm going to take care of this for you. We'll give it a shot.

Speaker 1: Mr. Benneman, I'm going to send these pills out. You'll see them come back at the end of the week.

Speaker 2: Let's see how we do, okay? Let's see how you like them, and then if they're similar to the old ones,

Speaker 1: I think it's the same manufacturer, but I'm going to send them.

Speaker 2: We'll do a little trial and error. I'm not going to charge you for them, and we'll see how we do, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, who am I speaking with?

Speaker 2: My name is Leo, L-E-O.

Speaker 1: L-E-O, and do you have an extension or anything?

Speaker 2: 0032.

Speaker 1: 0032, okay. Oh, so you can do that for me. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. Yep, so you're all set.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you, sir, and have a good day.

Speaker 2: You, too. Bye-bye.
